    "Modularity, or Q score, establishes the quality of the cluster division in the network and ranges from 0 to 1: a Q score greater than 0.3 denotes a well-organized network.",
    "Lastly, the quality of the clustering arrangement was evaluated with the silhouette score (S score), which ranges between -1 and + 1.",
    "Whether a network's S score is more than 0.3, 0.5, or 0.7 indicates it is homogeneous, acceptable, or very reliable [20].",
